### CSS 3D Transforms

**3D transforms** move elements in three-dimensional space.

---

### 3D Functions

| Function | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `translateZ(z)` | Move toward/away from viewer |
| `translate3d(x,y,z)` | Move in 3D space |
| `rotateX(angle)` | Rotate around X axis (horizontal) |
| `rotateY(angle)` | Rotate around Y axis (vertical) |
| `rotateZ(angle)` | Rotate around Z axis (same as 2D rotate) |
| `rotate3d(x,y,z,angle)` | Rotate around custom vector |
| `scaleZ(z)` | Scale along Z axis |
| `scale3d(x,y,z)` | Scale in 3D space |
| `perspective(n)` | Depth of 3D space |

---

### Perspective

**perspective** creates a 3D space. It determines how strong the 3D effect is:

```css
/* On parent (all children share perspective) */
.parent {
  perspective: 600px;
}

/* On individual element */
.element {
  transform: perspective(600px) rotateY(30deg);
}
```

Smaller `perspective` = more dramatic 3D effect.

---

### RotateX / RotateY / RotateZ

```css
.card:hover {
  transform: rotateX(30deg);  /* Tilt forward */
  transform: rotateY(30deg);  /* Turn to side */
  transform: rotateZ(30deg);  /* Spin (2D rotate) */
}
```

---

### TranslateZ

```css
.element {
  transform: translateZ(100px);  /* Closer to viewer */
  transform: translateZ(-100px); /* Further from viewer */
}
```

---

### Preserve 3D

```css
.parent {
  perspective: 800px;
  transform-style: preserve-3d; /* Children exist in 3D space */
}

.child {
  transform: rotateY(45deg);
}
```

Without `preserve-3d`, children are flattened.

---

### Backface Visibility

```css
.card-back {
  backface-visibility: hidden;   /* Hide when facing away */
  backface-visibility: visible;  /* Show (default) */
}
```

Useful for card flip effects.

---

### Card Flip Example

```css
.card {
  perspective: 1000px;
}

.card-inner {
  transform-style: preserve-3d;
  transition: transform 0.6s;
}

.card:hover .card-inner {
  transform: rotateY(180deg);
}

.card-front, .card-back {
  backface-visibility: hidden;
}

.card-back {
  transform: rotateY(180deg);
}
```

> **Key Point:** Always set `perspective` on the parent and `transform-style: preserve-3d` for children to be in 3D space.
